×031ATARI   Scene,   Results
========================×
The  Amiga scene is dominated by good designers - the
ATARI  scene  by  hardcore  coders  which  push their
machines   to   the   limits.

The  Atari was a coder's machine, while the Amiga was
an   artist's   machine.

they  have  a lot of people that may be focussed on a
very  small  range of computers, while we have a very
small  amount  of people working on a slightly larger
range   of   computers.

Demos  with  a menu is bliss for our nostalgia. Amiga
did   those   dentros/slideshows.

They  use  those  Amiga's,  and  we use those Atari's

The  Amiga  Scene  seems  to  be  focused  on 060 AGA
machines  only,  while  the  Atari  scene  is equally
active  on ST(E) (both oldskool and (c2p-) newskool),
Falcon'030   and   Falcon'060

Naturally  i'm  interested in checking out cool amiga
productions,  but  at  the  end  of the day they dont
bother  me  that much, and i dont keep myself updated
with  the  current  state  of  play  in their scenes.

The  Amiga  had a better marketing aswell a very good
blitter chip. Atari had its advantage when it came to
the  sound.  For  musicians Atari was the choice, but
demoscene  generally,  Atari  couldn't  match  up the
Amiga.

The  active  amiga  demoscene  is  not that large. It
